# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bootgly Docker — build context ignore (BuildKit, per-Dockerfile)
#
# Build context is the PARENT directory (/home/rodrigo/bootgly) so the `full`
# target can reach the sibling `bootgly_benchmarks/`. That parent holds many
# unrelated repos (bootgly_docs, bootgly_website, tmp, …) and multi-GB working
# data, so we ALLOWLIST: ignore everything, re-include only the paths the build
# needs, then re-ignore their heavy / irrelevant subpaths.
# Patterns are relative to the build context root (the parent directory).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# ? Ignore the entire context first
*

# ! Re-include only what the image is built from
!bootgly
!bootgly_benchmarks

# @ Trim bootgly/ — workdata is ~5.4G, tmp ~789M, vendor is rebuilt in-image
bootgly/.git
bootgly/.github
bootgly/.claude
bootgly/workdata
bootgly/tmp
bootgly/vendor
bootgly/public
bootgly/docs

# @ Trim bootgly_benchmarks/
bootgly_benchmarks/.git
bootgly_benchmarks/workdata
bootgly_benchmarks/scripts/.venv
# @ Keep competitor RUNTIMES out of the framework image (dependency-free).
#   The bench scripts/composer manifests stay; vendor/ + downloaded binaries do
#   not — the separate bootgly-bench image re-installs them per build ARG.
bootgly_benchmarks/**/vendor
bootgly_benchmarks/**/bootables/roadrunner/rr
bootgly_benchmarks/**/bootables/*/frankenphp

# @ Generic noise anywhere
**/.DS_Store
**/node_modules
**/*.log
**/.idea
**/.vscode
